	See our live coverage of the coronavirus outbreak for the latest news.



	As the number of known cases reached into the hundreds, then the thousands, then the hundreds of thousands, life all over the country has changed in profound ways. Malls, salons and dine-in restaurants have been forced to close or risk police action. High school proms, college graduations and professional sports have been cancelled or postponed. Many states have told people arriving from elsewhere to quarantine themselves. And even as politicians began partly reopening parts of the country, they have warned that the return to communal life would come in stages, and that the virus could surge anew in the months ahead.












